[This posting identifies the etiology of this hepatitis outbreak as hepatitis A. In the usual circumstances, hepatitis A in children tends to be mild, often totally without symptoms. In war torn Syria, however, with malnutrition and other stressors, increased morbidity and even mortality can occur.

